race.description: Fred Vella Tyre & Crash Repair Maiden Plate
race.comment: IMPENDING FURY (6) bounced back sharply last start when rising in trip, chasing with real purpose and only just missing. Backs up quickly and if he holds his form he can finally break through. SUNGAZER (7) took a solid step forward second-up over the mile at Seymour, sticking on gamely into third. The extra ground looks perfect now, and Toeroek's engagement is a strong pointer to his chances. CLARAPATRA (9) has found the shorter trips a shade sharp, so the rise in distance is ideal. Nearing peak fitness and capable of making her presence felt. ARLO'S DREAM (1) mixes his form, but his best efforts measure right up to this level. The wide draw isn't ideal, yet he holds claims and is worth keeping safe.
